The South African Police Service (SAPS) will hold a memorial service for slain top cop Lieutenant-Colonel Charl Kinnear in Belhar on the Cape Flats on Wednesday morning. A wreath laying ceremony will also take place in the area. The top Anti-Gang Unit investigator was gunned down outside his home more than a week ago. He was involved in probing high profile cases relating to the alleged criminal underworld. Former rugby player Zane Kilian has been charged with his murder. The video below, is reporting on Zane Kilian’s court appearance:  The Acting Western Cape Provincial Commissioner will be amongst those attending today’s memorial service.